value.value: A protein that is a translation product of the human BID gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human BAD gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human BAK1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The BAK2 gene is a recent duplication in humans and gives rise to a very similar protein.

A protein that is a translation product of the human BCL2, BCL2L1, or BCL2L2 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. The core domain architecture consists of an amino-terminal BH4 domain (Pfam:PF02180), which confers apoptosis inhibitory activity, and a Bcl-2 domain (Pfam:PF02180) common to many apoptosis regulator proteins.
A protein that is a translation product of the human BCL2L11 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human DFFA gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human FADD gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An AKT kinase that is a translation product of the human AKT1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A protein that is a translation product of a family of genes including the six human genes, TRAF1 to TRAF6. The core architectures of this protein consists of a zinc finger C3HC4 type (Ring finger) (Pfam:PF00097), a TRAF-type zinc finger (Pfam:PF02176) and a MATH domain (Pfam:PF00917).

label.value: staphylococcal enterotoxin C2, signal peptide removed form

value.value: A staphylococcal enterotoxin C2 that has had the signal peptide removed.
A protein that is a translation product of the human BAX gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. In this class the Bcl-2 domain is characterized by the presence of the BH3, BH1, and BH2 motifs.
A protein that is a translation product of the human APAF1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A protein that is a translation product of a family of genes that includes CASP1, CASP2, CASP4, CASP5, CASP9 and others. The core architecture consists of a Caspase recruitment domain (Pfam:PF00619), Caspase domain (Pfam:PF00656) and a PAAD/DAPIN/Pyrin domain (Pfam:PF02758). Encoded as zymogens, the activated proteins are cysteine proteases typically involved in apoptosis.

A protein that is a translation product of a gene family that includes CASP3, CASP6, and CASP7 genes. The core architecture consists of a Caspase domain (Pfam:PF00656). Encoded as zymogens, the activated proteins are cysteine proteases typically involved in apoptosis.

A protein that is a translation product of the human CASP8, CASP10, or CFLAR genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. The core domain architecture consists of two consecutive copies of the Death effector domain (DED) domain (Pfam:PF01335) in an amino-terminal propeptide followed by Peptidase_C14 domain (Pfam:PF00656). Encoded as zymogens, the activated proteins are cysteine proteases typically involved in apoptosis.
A protein that is a translation product of the human CTNNB1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the CYC, CYCS or closely related CYCT gene (mouse and rat) with core architecture consisting of a Cytochrome c (Pfam:PF00034) domain.
A TEC-type tyrosine-protein kinase that is a translation product of the human BMX gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A protein that is a translation product of the human DYNLL1 or DYNLL2 genes, or 1:1 orthologs thereof. The protein is small (89 residues in human and mouse) with core architecture consisting of a Dynein light chain type 1 domain (Pfam:PF01221).
A protein that is a translation product of the human GSN gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human NMT1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A lymphotoxin that is a translation product of the human LTA gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A lymphotoxin that is a translation product of the human LTB gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human MAPK8 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human OCLN gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human PSMB2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human PSMB4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A protein that is a translation product of the human PRKCD, PRKCE, PRKCH, or PRKCQ genes, or 1:1 orthologs thereof. The core domain architecture consists of a C2 domain (Pfam:PF00168), which is not always detected, two Phorbol esters/diacylglycerol binding domains (Pfam:PF00130, also called C1 domain), a Protein kinase domain (Pfam:PF00069), and a Protein kinase C terminal domain (Pfam:PF00433).
A protein that is a translation product of the human ARHGAP10 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of a family of genes that includes STK24, STK25, or STK26. The core architecture consists of one Protein kinase domain (Pfam:PF00069).
A protein that is a translation product of the Staphylococcus aureus entC3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
